I only have 214MB left on my hard drive. I'm kind of new to this can some one tell me how bad that is .How can I cut down on the size of my pics and not lessen the quality of my pics. And can I save my pics on a 3 ½ floppy. How much space is on a 3 ½ floppy any how. <br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/uwhitemage.showPublicProfile?language=EN>WhiteMage</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(7/12/01 12:46:46 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://ffwafanart.homestead.com/files/amano_avatar.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Disk space. Need help </span><hr size=1> I would avoid using floppy disks at all costs.  You're better off to just delete it, since that's what you're doing if you put it on a floppy.  I'd suggest, if you really need the space, to take a look at what else is on your computer...have you got 40 gillion mp3's and half a dozen video games?  Also, what are you usually saving your pics as?  .jpg files don't take up very much space, and there isn't *that* much quality loss. <p><a href=http://darkhalo.sphosting.com>d a r k h a l o</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/ushousetsu.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Shousetsu</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.newelysium.com/forum/psicon.gif width=13 height=13 BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Moderator</span><br> <font color=#336699>(7/12/01 1:42:56 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.newelysium.com/forum/photo.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Disk space. Need help </span><hr size=1> uninstall some games or other stuff you dont use on your computer anymore to free up a lot of space. You can always reinstall them later if you need them.<br>
<br>
image files take up little to no space, 214mbs is enough to store a lifetime of images, so theres no need to do anything different than what your doing now. But you will need to uninstall some big programs you never use because 216mbs is barely anything if you want to add new programs to your computer some day. <p><a href="http://www.newelysium.com"><img src="http://www.newelysium.com/banners/newelysium4.gif" border=0></a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/uflintpaper.showPublicProfile?language=EN>FlintPaper</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(7/12/01 7:30:07 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://fppd.xoasis.com/fpicon02.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Disk space. Need help </span><hr size=1> I ran into a HD space crunch recently. What you really need is to do a bit of &quot;cleaning house.&quot;  A way to cut down on image size is to save images less that 256 colors as *.GIF's. I've had good results with that.  <br>
<br>
Back to cleaning house - you really need to dump anything you don't use or need. If you're running Windows, you probably have a ton of its crap installed. Go to Control Panel, Add\Remove Programs and then click on the Windows Setup tab. Go through all the categories and purge as neccesary. You'd be suprised how much disk-space you can free that way.<br>
<br>
Never use floppies for storage unless it's a last resort.  Floppies these days are all 1.44 MB (used to have 720 k as well). Little space coupled with slow access speed make them a poor option for storage.<br>
<br>
If you can't free up any space or you're hard-drive is small to begin with it my be time to upgrade. You likely won't need and 40 or 30 gig one and you can get a good price if you shop around. It's pretty easy to install a new drive and you can keep your old one as a secondary. Check out <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.help.com">www.help.com</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> at CNET for tutorials on how to do this. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/ushousetsu.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Shousetsu</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.newelysium.com/forum/psicon.gif width=13 height=13 BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Moderator</span><br> <font color=#336699>(7/12/01 8:03:58 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://www.newelysium.com/forum/photo.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Disk space. Need help </span><hr size=1> most images will actually be larger in file size if you save them as a gif rather than jpg, because JPG can do compression. <p><a href="http://www.newelysium.com"><img src="http://www.newelysium.com/banners/newelysium4.gif" border=0></a></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/ushousetsu.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Shousetsu</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC=http://www.newelysium.com/forum/psicon.gif width=13 height=13 BORDER=0> at: 7/12/01 8:04:39 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/uanime647web.showPublicProfile?language=EN>anime647web</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(7/13/01 5:35:05 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Disk space. Need help </span><hr size=1> Thanks I've been working on cleaning up. <br>
